## <a id="_gj6hfw86yoez"></a>Corporate Overview

Prompt: Create a 2,000\-word article that describes the history and business of Discuss\.io that is suitable for a VC investor\.

### <a id="_s442r16p2cvb"></a>Introduction

In an era where data\-driven decision\-making is paramount, understanding consumer behavior and preferences is critical for businesses\. Discuss\.io, a leading platform in the qualitative research space, has carved out a niche by enabling companies to conduct real\-time, in\-depth consumer conversations and insights\. This article provides an extensive overview of Discuss\.io, detailing its history, business model, competitive landscape, and future prospects to offer venture capital investors a comprehensive understanding of the company\.

### <a id="_5vrofibx2xgu"></a>__History and Evolution__

Founding and Early Days

Discuss\.io was founded in 2012 by Zach Simmons\. The company emerged from Simmons' vision of transforming the market research industry through technology\. The traditional methods of conducting focus groups and consumer interviews were often slow, costly, and limited by geographical constraints\. Simmons recognized the potential of the internet to overcome these challenges by creating a platform that could connect researchers with participants globally in real time\.

Initial Growth and Development

The initial years saw Discuss\.io focusing on developing a robust and user\-friendly platform\. The company aimed to offer a seamless experience for both researchers and participants\. Early on, they incorporated features such as live video interviews, transcription services, and real\-time collaboration tools\. This innovative approach quickly gained traction, and Discuss\.io began to attract clients from various industries looking for more efficient ways to gather consumer insights\.

Key Milestones

- 2014: Discuss\.io launched its first version of the platform, which included basic video conferencing and transcription capabilities\.
- 2016: The company secured its Series A funding, which allowed for significant expansion of its technology and team\.
- 2018: Discuss\.io introduced AI\-driven insights and analytics, enhancing the depth and value of the data collected through its platform\.
- 2020: Amid the COVID\-19 pandemic, the demand for virtual qualitative research surged, positioning Discuss\.io as a critical tool for businesses navigating the new normal\. The company expanded its client base significantly and continued to innovate its product offerings\.

### <a id="_cysjywn3lpbc"></a>__Business Model and Services__

Platform Overview

Discuss\.io offers a cloud\-based platform that facilitates live video interviews, focus groups, and other qualitative research activities\. The platform is designed to be user\-friendly, providing researchers with all the tools they need to conduct effective interviews and gather valuable insights\.

Core Services

1. Live Video Interviews: High\-quality video conferencing capabilities allow researchers to conduct interviews and focus groups with participants from anywhere in the world\. The platform supports multiple participants, making it ideal for group discussions\.
2. Transcription and Translation: Discuss\.io provides real\-time transcription services, making it easy for researchers to capture and analyze conversations\. Translation services are also available for international studies, ensuring that language barriers do not impede research efforts\.
3. AI\-Driven Insights: Leveraging artificial intelligence, Discuss\.io offers advanced analytics tools that help researchers identify patterns and extract actionable insights from qualitative data\. This includes sentiment analysis, keyword extraction, and thematic analysis\.
4. Collaboration Tools: The platform includes features that facilitate collaboration among research teams, such as shared notes, live chat, and project management tools\. This ensures that teams can work together efficiently, regardless of their physical location\.
5. Participant Recruitment: Discuss\.io provides a robust participant recruitment service, connecting researchers with a diverse pool of participants that meet their specific criteria\. This service ensures that studies are conducted with the right target audience, enhancing the relevance and reliability of the findings\.

Revenue Model

Discuss\.io operates on a subscription\-based revenue model\. Clients can choose from various subscription tiers based on their needs, with options for small teams to large enterprises\. Additionally, the company offers pay\-per\-use services for specific features like transcription, translation, and participant recruitment\. This flexible pricing strategy caters to a wide range of clients, from startups to multinational corporations\.

### <a id="_idcufr8n0enm"></a>__Competitive Landscape__

Market Position

Discuss\.io is positioned as a leader in the qualitative research technology market\. The company's focus on innovation and customer\-centric solutions has allowed it to stand out in a crowded space\. Key competitors include UserTesting, FocusVision, and Remesh, each offering unique features and capabilities\.

Differentiators

1. User Experience: Discuss\.io prioritizes a seamless user experience, ensuring that both researchers and participants can use the platform with ease\. This focus on usability has resulted in high customer satisfaction and retention rates\.
2. AI and Analytics: The incorporation of AI\-driven insights sets Discuss\.io apart from many competitors\. These advanced analytics tools provide deeper and more actionable insights, enhancing the value of the research conducted on the platform\.
3. Global Reach: Discuss\.io's ability to connect researchers with participants from around the world is a significant advantage\. This global reach allows for more diverse and representative studies, which are crucial for businesses operating in multiple markets\.
4. Comprehensive Services: The company's all\-in\-one platform approach, which includes participant recruitment, transcription, translation, and collaboration tools, provides a complete solution for qualitative research\. This reduces the need for clients to use multiple vendors and simplifies the research process\.

### <a id="_l79gpwamvo59"></a>

### <a id="_36xdq8nauy4h"></a>__Financial Performance and Funding__

Revenue Growth

Discuss\.io has demonstrated impressive revenue growth since its inception\. The company's subscription\-based model has provided a stable and recurring revenue stream, while the increasing demand for virtual research solutions has driven significant growth in recent years\.

Funding Rounds

Discuss\.io has successfully raised several funding rounds to support its growth and expansion:

- Series A \(2016\): The company raised $4\.5 million to enhance its platform and expand its team\.
- Series B \(2019\): Discuss\.io secured $10 million to accelerate its AI and analytics capabilities and expand its market reach\.

Profitability

While Discuss\.io has focused heavily on growth and innovation, the company has also made strides toward profitability\. Efficient cost management and the high scalability of its platform have contributed to improving profit margins\. Discuss\.io is on track to achieve sustainable profitability as it continues to expand its customer base and enhance its service offerings\.

### <a id="_vjmnfdn13mpt"></a>__Strategic Partnerships and Collaborations__

Industry Collaborations

Discuss\.io has formed strategic partnerships with various industry players to enhance its platform and expand its reach\. These collaborations include:

- Technology Partners: Collaborations with leading technology providers have enabled Discuss\.io to integrate advanced features and improve the overall functionality of its platform\. For example, partnerships with AI and machine learning companies have enhanced the platform's analytics capabilities\.
- Market Research Firms: Partnering with established market research firms has allowed Discuss\.io to tap into new client bases and offer its technology as a value\-added service\. These partnerships have also facilitated knowledge sharing and best practices, further enhancing Discuss\.io's offerings\.
- Academic Institutions: Collaborations with universities and research institutions have helped Discuss\.io stay at the forefront of qualitative research methodologies and technologies\. These partnerships have also provided opportunities for joint research projects and thought leadership initiatives\.

Customer Success Stories

Discuss\.io boasts a diverse client portfolio, including some of the world's leading brands\. Notable success stories include:

- Consumer Goods: A multinational consumer goods company used Discuss\.io to conduct global focus groups, leading to the successful launch of a new product line\. The insights gathered through the platform helped the company understand regional preferences and tailor its marketing strategies accordingly\.
- Healthcare: A leading pharmaceutical company leveraged Discuss\.io's platform to gather patient feedback on a new medication\. The qualitative data collected played a crucial role in refining the product and developing targeted communication strategies for healthcare professionals and patients\.
- Technology: A major tech company utilized Discuss\.io to conduct user experience research for a new software product\. The real\-time insights and feedback helped the company make iterative improvements, resulting in a more user\-friendly and successful product launch\.

### <a id="_fx4qqoh0gjbs"></a>__Future Prospects__

Market Opportunities

The market for qualitative research technology is poised for significant growth\. As businesses increasingly recognize the value of consumer insights in driving innovation and strategic decisions, the demand for efficient and scalable research solutions is expected to rise\. Key opportunities for Discuss\.io include:

- Expanding into New Industries: While Discuss\.io already serves a diverse range of industries, there are opportunities to further penetrate sectors such as finance, education, and government\. These industries are increasingly seeking innovative ways to gather and analyze qualitative data\.
- Geographical Expansion: Discuss\.io can continue to expand its global footprint, particularly in emerging markets where digital transformation is accelerating\. Establishing a presence in these regions can open up new revenue streams and client bases\.
- Product Innovation: Ongoing investment in AI and machine learning technologies can further enhance Discuss\.io's platform, offering even deeper insights and more automated processes\. Developing new features and tools that address specific client needs will continue to drive customer acquisition and retention\.

Challenges and Risks

As with any growing company, Discuss\.io faces certain challenges and risks:

- Competition: The qualitative research technology market is competitive, with new entrants constantly emerging\. Discuss\.io must continue to innovate and differentiate its offerings to maintain its market position\.
- Data Security and Privacy: Ensuring the security and privacy of the data collected through its platform is critical\. Any breaches or lapses could damage Discuss\.io's reputation and result in regulatory penalties\.
- Scalability: As Discuss\.io continues to grow, maintaining the scalability and reliability of its platform will be essential\. Ensuring that the infrastructure can handle increasing volumes of data and users is a key challenge\.

Strategic Initiatives

To address these opportunities and challenges, Discuss\.io has outlined several strategic initiatives:

- R&D Investment: Continued investment in research and development will drive product innovation and maintain Discuss\.io's competitive edge\. This includes enhancing AI capabilities, developing new features, and improving the overall user experience\.
- Market Expansion: Discuss\.io plans to expand its sales and marketing efforts to reach new clients and industries\. This includes targeted campaigns, strategic partnerships, and exploring new geographic markets\.
- Operational Excellence: Focusing on operational efficiency and scalability will ensure that Discuss\.io can continue to deliver high\-quality services as it grows\. This includes investing in infrastructure, optimizing processes, and expanding the team\.

### <a id="_c8uuj2lhtj9n"></a>__Conclusion__

Discuss\.io stands out as a leader in the qualitative research technology space, offering a comprehensive and innovative platform that meets the evolving needs of businesses seeking consumer insights\. With a strong history of growth, a robust business model, and a clear strategic vision, Discuss\.io is well\-positioned to capitalize on the expanding market opportunities\.

For venture capital investors, Discuss\.io represents a compelling investment opportunity\. The company's proven track record, innovative technology, and focus on customer success provide a solid foundation for continued growth and profitability\. By investing in Discuss\.io, investors can be part of a transformative journey that is reshaping the market research industry and driving data\-driven decision\-making for businesses worldwide\.

### <a id="_93grs6mm1vpi"></a>[Genie](https://www.discuss.io/platform/generative-ai/)

G__*enie is positioned as a generative AI platform\. It runs on Azure’s OpenAI platform which is interesting\. Discuss’ roots trace back to AWS which is where the built their video conferencing technology\. Being based in Seattle, however, has led to some Microsoft connections\. *__

#### <a id="_x5d8hj3y00qo"></a>Create reports that drive decisions faster

Spend less time analyzing your findings and more time delivering impactful insights\. With Genie, turn around insights instantly so you can make faster decisions\. With a generative AI assistant, you can:

- Summarize live and asynchronous research
- Highlight project\-level themes & quotes
- Find quotes & summaries to a specific question
- Suggest or auto\-magically create highlight reels

__*Genie’s summarization and thematic analysis capabilities are classic GenAI capabilities\. They have standard analysis formats, but a user can enter a prompt like statement describing what they want\. The system then translates that statement into a classic prompt and executes it\.*__

#### <a id="_mx9pv2vs4tmu"></a>Find and screen target audiences more efficiently

Finding the right respondents can be time\-consuming and complex\. In the future, Genie will be able to help you get started so you can shorten your setup time with the ability to:

- Develop personas
- Identify segments
- Create screeners
- Follow up on pre\-work

#### <a id="_xzcjakjpbket"></a>Maximize engagement to collect more in\-depth feedback

Turn anyone into a qualitative expert\. To scale qualitative research, you need an assistant who allows you to seamlessly collect in\-depth feedback from your target audience\. In the future, Genie will:

- Improve discussion guides
- Generate asynchronous activities
- Save key moments
- Improve moderation skills

### <a id="_33kx96fx9e5z"></a>Insights

#### <a id="_gyesx4hicbqs"></a>Auto\-generate clips based on keyword tags

No more scrubbing hours of videos to find clips associated to specific keywords\. Use our video organization, editing and sharing capabilities to make the most out of your project video library\.

Leverage our theme finding capabilities to scan any video uploaded to your Discuss project, whether from a live interview or an uploaded Zoom, Teams, or __other interview platform\. __Auto\-generate clips based on keywords or tags that you create\!

Learn how Augmented Insights’ AI\-enabled capabilities work in five easy steps\.

#### <a id="_chizp85nxlzf"></a>Saving 'aha' moments has never been easier

Our Saved Moment feature captures 30 seconds of magic during your video interviews, but you may save dozens \(or hundreds\) of clips during a project\. Our real\-time tagging feature helps you organize clips around recommended, pre\-built or on\-the\-fly tags\. This feature also works with any videos you upload from any source into the project as part of your CX Collection\.

Observers and moderators can both tag the saved moments in the meeting room and our tag explorer helps you filter and find the clips that tell the story you want to tell\. Clients using tags cut their insights generation time in half and actively share many more clips

Theme Finder

Auto\-generate video clips from any video uploaded to the Discuss platform based on pre\-selected or new keyword tags\.

Saved Moments

A click of the Save Moments button captures 15 seconds before and after that moment as a clip and stored in your recordings for later\.

Word Cloud

We use the tags from saved moments and theme finder video clips to create word cloud visual to highlight more important keywords\.

Understanding the mobile user journey is critical when it comes to providing better customer and user experiences\. See how your audience is interacting with your site in real time and gain invaluable user feedback\.

#### <a id="_qqaux6a44rqi"></a>Integrated with our People Experience Platform

Our mobile screen share capability is an extension of the Discuss platform\. This means that all of the pre\-, during and post\-session features we’ve built are part of the Mobile UX interview\. See and hear the user, record and translate the conversation, and share clips with your team\.

#### <a id="_cr251aoq26qf"></a>Download App

Respondent downloads app for free from iOS iTunes or Google Play stores for free\.

#### <a id="_mptdh7wx3snu"></a>Enter Secure Code

The respondent can either enter a unique code for the interview session, or scan a QR code when entering — this prompts them to download the app and enter the meeting room directly\.

#### <a id="_nsfo4wobcqyd"></a>Share Mobile Screen

The moderator allows the respondent screen to be shared in the meeting room and the mobile experience interview continues\.

__*Mobile Screen Share was developed in response to requirements from Unilever\. It is not a major focus or shift into the app research space like UserTesting, UserZoom, or Maze\.*__

## <a id="_734w5e1hpjcf"></a>Discuss Compliance with German Data/Privacy Regulations

In our role as a data processor, Discuss offers the following functionality to help customers stay compliant with German data privacy regulations for their Live Qual Research\.

Respondent Location \- When an interview is scheduled, the scheduler is required to set the respondents’ location\. This allows Discuss to detect interviews with German data subjects and provide proper anonymization

Meeting Room Pseudonyms \- Respondents and moderators appear with pseudonyms rather than real names to protect privacy\. Phone users are anonymized and phone numbers are never visible\. Learn more 

Private Chat \- Sensitive data can be shared with tech support via private chat for troubleshooting\. All chat messages can be deleted when no longer needed\. Private chats are not visible to project members after the interview and can be requested by contacting customercare@discuss\.io Learn more

Anonymized Video Recordings \- All German interviews are anonymized in post\-processing, ensuring faces are not identifiable in the final recording\. Researchers can interact on video during the interview, but recordings, stimuli, and screen shares are blurred and cannot be unblurred\. Whiteboard snapshots remain clear\. Learn more

Audio\-Only Interviews \- We also offer audio\-only interviews, in which the webcam never comes on\. This allows researchers to utilize all the meeting room functionality like Saved Moments, Discussion Guides, integrated translation, and private chat while providing an extra layer of privacy when live video is not required\. Learn more

Restrict Observer Audio \- When there's a session with a simultaneous translator, observers will ONLY be able to hear the translator's audio and not the main meeting room\. This is useful to protect the audio of the respondents\. Learn more

Disable Recording \- This feature allows disabling recordings at the project or interview level\. Clients can choose to override all interviews or apply the setting only to new ones from their Project Settings\. The recording status for each session can be viewed in the Recording column under the Overview tab\. In the meeting room, the Help\! button remains available if Live Support is included\. Learn more

All interviews must include a respondent country when they are scheduled\. When this country is set to Germany, recordings will be anonymized automatically\. No further action is needed\. If you are doing a multi\-country interview, and there are any participants from Germany, the respondent location should be set to Germany to maintain compliance\.

Can I undo anonymization in German interviews?

Due to privacy restrictions, it is not possible to turn off the usage of pseudonyms in the meeting room or to maintain non\-anonymized recordings\. Once a recording is anonymized, it cannot be reversed\.

Can I anonymize other interviews, not just German ones?

Our Privacy & Security features are appropriate for many types of interviews, especially when highly sensitive information will be discussed or due to industry regulations\. The features are available as a setting on every Discuss project\.

 

Project members have separate options to blur videos and/or to anonymize respondent/moderator names\. Collaborators & Editors can turn this on by visiting the Settings tab of their project and checking the appropriate box\. This feature must be turned on prior to an interview starting, and once anonymized, a recording cannot be reversed\.

 

Please note that turning this checkbox off will not impact the anonymization of interviews in Germany, which users cannot turn off\.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

 

What happens to my stimuli if recordings are blurred?

Stimuli are blurred

Mobile Screenshare is blurred

Whiteboard snapshot aren’t blurred

The setting can be turned off at any time by project members, and future recordings in that project will not be anonymized\. 

If the option to blur recordings is enabled, project members will also be able to also apply blurring to previous interviews or to media upload from the recordings tab\. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

 

How do you notify team members of this requirement?

Users are notified of these requirements if they select Germany as a country when using our interactive quote app\. In addition, any user scheduling an interview will be notified when they set the respondent country to Germany\.

Project owners receive an email detailing our anonymization features when their project kicks off in Germany, and project members viewing recordings will see an informational note explaining why the recordings are anonymized\.

# <a id="_hfjwyh81yh57"></a>Pricing

Discuss\.io's plans are structured around several tiers, each offering a range of features and services to support qualitative research:

- Pro: This plan includes core features necessary for research projects\.
- Premium: This plan adds live support for enhanced customer service and is popular among agencies\.
- Premium \+: This plan offers project management services, allowing users to focus on research while Discuss\.io handles logistical aspects\.
- Consumer Reach: This comprehensive plan provides fully\-managed end\-to\-end research support, ideal for brands looking to leverage extensive services including recruitment and respondent incentives​ \(Discuss\)​​ \(Zendesk Support\)​​ \(SaaSworthy\)​\.
- Each plan can be further customized to include additional services such as asynchronous research, off\-platform research, observer access, and moderator network access\. 

Discuss\.io also offers generative AI assistant services to streamline the research process and provide faster insights\.
